Delegate:
---------
Delegate is a base class for all the delegates.
Delegates are commonly used for call back functions or event handlings.

Action:
----------
Action is a predefined generic delegate that will not retun any value as output.

Action will accept upto 16 input of different datatypes. The return type of Action delegate is 'void'.

Func:
-------
Func is also a predefined generic delegate type which will return value as output.
It also accept 16 inputs with different data types and retun one output.

Example: Func<int, int, int> myFunc = (x, y) => x + y;
